🚀 Getting Started
Prerequisites

Java 17+
Maven 3.8+
An OpenAI API Key

1. Clone the repository
bashgit clone https://github.com/kumarramtech/SpringAI.git
cd SpringAI/openai
2. Configure your OpenAI API Key
In src/main/resources/application.properties:
propertiesspring.ai.openai.api-key=YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY
spring.ai.openai.chat.options.model=gpt-4
spring.ai.openai.chat.options.temperature=0.7

⚠️ Never commit your API key. Use environment variables or a secrets manager in production.

3. Build and Run
bashmvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run
The application starts on http://localhost:8080

📡 API Endpoints
Chat with AI
httpGET /ai/chat?message=What is Spring AI?
Response:
json{
  "response": "Spring AI is an application framework for AI engineering..."
}
Prompt Template
httpGET /ai/prompt?topic=microservices&language=Java

💡 Example Usage
bashcurl "http://localhost:8080/ai/chat?message=Explain+event-driven+architecture+in+banking"

